            },
            "answer_text": "The [H+] ion Concentration of the acid Solution with pH= 6 is = 10^-6MIf we dilute 100- times the concentration of the acid Solution will be 10^-6 /100= 10^-8 M.Since neutral water always contains 10^-7 M of H + ions, the concentration of the diluted acid Solution will be ( 10^-7 + 10^-8) M =(1x10^-7 +0.1 x 10^-7)= 1.01 x 10^-7 MSo pH = - log (1.1 x 10^-7)=6.9586.{Note: Since on dilution the concentration of the solution becomes 10^-8, the Solution's pH will not be equal to 8.Because on dilution an acid Solution will become a weak acid,but NEVER BECOME BASIC OR ALKALINE in nature}",
